Cookie policy.



What are cookies?
Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device by websites that you visit. They are widely used in order to make websites work, or work more efficiently, as well as to provide information to the owners of the site.
The categories of cookies used on LGIM.com by Legal & General Investment Management Limited, One Coleman Street, London EC2R 5AA are the following:

Strictly necessary
Performance
Functionality and
Targeting.

These categories are based on the International UK Chamber of Commerce Cookie Guide. You can find more information about the individual cookies we use and the purposes for which we use them in the table below.


CookieLife spanFunction1st or 3rd partyCategory

Adobe Omniture
Session
Site analytics.
3rd
